  "texts": [
    "Right: Training accuracy over 2000 epochs for LoRA, FourierFT, and MaCP.",
    "Although all methods use the same number of trainable parameters, LoRA exhibits significant oscillations and fails to converge to 100% accuracy, indicating performance bottlenecks.",
    "FourierFT quickly reaches near-perfect accuracy within 500 epochs with stable performance.",
    "Our proposed MaCP approach outperforms both methods by converging faster (around 450 epochs) and maintaining higher accuracy with minimal fluctuations.",
    "lowing (Sung et al., 2022), VL-BART is fine-tuned in a multi-task setup."
